{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017fPBNWeTs5u3sXhVujrbjQ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: \"PRD-227.6\"\n3\ttitle: \"Define SYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE\"\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: medium\n7\teffort: s\n8\tcapability: moderate\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-227-workflow-templates]]\"\n10\tdepends_on:\n11\t  - \"[[PRD-227.1-core-workflow-template]]\"\n12\tblocks: []\n13\timpacts:\n14\t  - src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py\n15\t  - tests/test_workflow_templates.py\n16\tworkflow: null\n17\ttarget_version: null\n18\tcreated: 2026-04-08\n19\tupdated: 2026-04-08\n20\ttags:\n21\t  - harness\n22\t  - workflow\n23\t---\n24\t\n25\t# Define SYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE\n26\t\n27\t## Summary\n28\t\n29\tDefine `SYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE` for non-PRD-bound system operations (PRD-223). System operations have a different lifecycle: they acquire a global lock on open, and release it + write a report file on close. No PR creation, no status transitions â€” system ops aren't tied to PRD state.\n30\t\n31\t## Requirements\n32\t\n33\t1. Define `SYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE` in `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py`.\n34\t2. Opening tasks:\n35\t   - `acquire_global_lock` â€” prevent concurrent system operations\n36\t   - `log_operation_start` â€” record the operation start time and context\n37\t3. Closing tasks:\n38\t   - `write_report` â€” write an operation report file\n39\t   - `log_operation_end` â€” record completion\n40\t   - `release_global_lock` â€” release the lock acquired on open\n41\t4. Middle allows `ShellTask` and `AgentTask`; no minimum count constraints (some system ops may be pure shell).\n42\t5. Add tests for the system operation template's compose/validation behavior.\n43\t\n44\t## Technical Approach\n45\t\n46\t### `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py`\n47\t\n48\t```python\n49\tSYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE = WorkflowTemplate(\n50\t    name=\"system-operation\",\n51\t    description=\"System operation lifecycle: lock, execute, report, unlock.\",\n52\t    open=[\n53\t        BuiltIn(\"acquire_global_lock\"),\n54\t        BuiltIn(\"log_operation_start\"),\n55\t    ],\n56\t    middle_kinds=[AgentTask, ShellTask],\n57\t    middle_required={},\n58\t    close=[\n59\t        BuiltIn(\"write_report\"),\n60\t        BuiltIn(\"log_operation_end\"),\n61\t        BuiltIn(\"release_global_lock\"),\n62\t    ],\n63\t)\n64\t```\n65\t\n66\t### Tests\n67\t\n68\t- Valid composition produces `[lock, log_start, *middle, report, log_end, unlock]`\n69\t- Empty middle is allowed (middle_required is empty)\n70\t- Disallowed task types in middle raise `TemplateViolation`\n71\t\n72\t## Acceptance Criteria\n73\t\n74\t- [ ] AC-1: `SYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE` is importable from `darkfactory.templates_builtin`.\n75\t- [ ] AC-2: The template's close list includes `release_global_lock` as the final task.\n76\t- [ ] AC-3: The template's open list includes `acquire_global_lock` as the first task.\n77\t- [ ] AC-4: Composing with an empty middle succeeds (no minimum count constraints).\n78\t- [ ] AC-5: Test coverage for valid composition and kind violations.\n79\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c2db0b7-c6f6-4557-b4ef-b7756a316e55","uuid":"0ae7054f-33e0-4908-b371-282887105513","timestamp":"2026-04-09T04:40:19.692Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.darkfactory/prds/PRD-227.6-system-operation-template.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-227.6\"\ntitle: \"Define SYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: s\ncapability: moderate\nparent: \"[[PRD-227-workflow-templates]]\"\ndepends_on:\n  - \"[[PRD-227.1-core-workflow-template]]\"\nblocks: []\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py\n  - tests/test_workflow_templates.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - harness\n  - workflow\n---\n\n# Define SYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine `SYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE` for non-PRD-bound system operations (PRD-223). System operations have a different lifecycle: they acquire a global lock on open, and release it + write a report file on close. No PR creation, no status transitions â€” system ops aren't tied to PRD state.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Define `SYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE` in `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py`.\n2. Opening tasks:\n   - `acquire_global_lock` â€” prevent concurrent system operations\n   - `log_operation_start` â€” record the operation start time and context\n3. Closing tasks:\n   - `write_report` â€” write an operation report file\n   - `log_operation_end` â€” record completion\n   - `release_global_lock` â€” release the lock acquired on open\n4. Middle allows `ShellTask` and `AgentTask`; no minimum count constraints (some system ops may be pure shell).\n5. Add tests for the system operation template's compose/validation behavior.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/templates_builtin.py`\n\n```python\nSYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE = WorkflowTemplate(\n    name=\"system-operation\",\n    description=\"System operation lifecycle: lock, execute, report, unlock.\",\n    open=[\n        BuiltIn(\"acquire_global_lock\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"log_operation_start\"),\n    ],\n    middle_kinds=[AgentTask, ShellTask],\n    middle_required={},\n    close=[\n        BuiltIn(\"write_report\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"log_operation_end\"),\n        BuiltIn(\"release_global_lock\"),\n    ],\n)\n```\n\n### Tests\n\n- Valid composition produces `[lock, log_start, *middle, report, log_end, unlock]`\n- Empty middle is allowed (middle_required is empty)\n- Disallowed task types in middle raise `TemplateViolation`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `SYSTEM_OPERATION_TEMPLATE` is importable from `darkfactory.templates_builtin`.\n- [ ] AC-2: The template's close list includes `release_global_lock` as the final task.\n- [ ] AC-3: The template's open list includes `acquire_global_lock` as the first task.\n- [ ] AC-4: Composing with an empty middle succeeds (no minimum count constraints).\n- [ ] AC-5: Test coverage for valid composition and kind violations.\n","numLines":79,"startLine":1,"totalLines":79}}}
